										<h3>About this talk</h3>
										<p id="tagline"  >What was the greatest invention of the industrial revolution? Hans Rosling makes the case for the washing machine. With newly designed graphics from Gapminder, Rosling shows us the magic that pops up when economic growth and electricity turn a boring wash day into an intellectual day of reading.</p>
											<div id="attributionText">
													</div>
															<h3>About Hans Rosling</h3>
					<p>
					In Hans Rosling’s hands, data sings. Global trends in health and economics come to vivid life. And the big picture of global development—with some surprisingly good news—snaps into sharp focus. <a target="_blank" class="external" href="/speakers/hans_rosling.html">Full bio and more links</a>					</p>
										<div id="adSpace"></div>
